<subSubSection id="C37502E6132FFFCABC9D687C6E4DFE88" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="296" pageId="8" pageNumber="293" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD0516D132FFFCABC9D687C6E4DFE88" blockId="8.[677,1210,1497,1704]" lastBlockId="11.[113,646,205,280]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="296" pageId="8" pageNumber="293">DIAGNOSIS. — Club-shaped sponge with shallow depression at the upper pole in which a cluster of rounded openings of short canals occurs. Desmas are tripodial strongly tuberculated with the upper conical ray bearing no articulation. Desmas articulation nonterminal. No dermalia have been observed.</paragraph>
